        <mxCell id="iDT1CfoRDI9vFV7TsdX0-30" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;spacingTop=0;spacingLeft=9;fillColor=default;strokeColor=default;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Flows&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-start=&quot;568&quot; data-end=&quot;598&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Direct UI Transaction Flow&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;screens | forms → APIs → DB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;605&quot; data-end=&quot;641&quot;&gt;2. Agent-Orchestrated Mutation Flow&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;chat | commands → Agentic Orchestrator → APIs → DB&lt;br data-start=&quot;641&quot; data-end=&quot;644&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span data-start=&quot;648&quot; data-end=&quot;700&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. Agent-Orchestrated Semantic Retrieval (RAG) Flow&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;chat | commands → Agentic Orchestrator → RAG → (Vector Index + DB)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="194" width="438" x="194" y="173" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="iDT1CfoRDI9vFV7TsdX0-22" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="Agentic&lt;div&gt;Orchestrator&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="120" x="120" y="630" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="iDT1CfoRDI9vFV7TsdX0-37" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="The application is a production-style system used to manage core domain data and user workflows through a web interface. It exposes functionality through structured data models, forms, and APIs (CRUD), while also storing information across multiple related records and unstructured fields. This architecture diagram exposes the manual transaction flow as well as&amp;nbsp;an agentic layer that translates natural language requests into read (query/RAG) and write (CRUD) operations against the existing application stack, without altering core business logic." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="103" width="621" x="103" y="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
